  "texts": [
    "In comparison, operation-based cybersecurity training programs emphasize practical, hands-on activities aimed at enhancing participants' technical skills and abilities.",
    "These exercises take place in simulated, emulated, physical, or hybrid practice environments.",
    "Recent studies have found that the creation of these practice environments, known as cyber-ranges, often relies on manual setup and configuration.",
    "This approach is not only ineffective but also prone to errors, making it a tedious process [8].",
    "A similar approach was introduced by C. Chindrus et al. [9], their research study proposed a practical approach to enhancing cybersecurity readiness through a simulated 'Red' and 'Blue' cybersecurity competition."
  ],
